  abstract = {Digital predistortion (DPD) has become indispensable for linearizing RF power amplifiers (PAs), particularly in broadband applications. This work proposes T-Trans DPD, a novel DPD architecture that combines Transformer networks with temporal convolutional networks (TCN), achieving superior linearization on both digital PA (DPA) and analog PA (APA). Evaluated on the OpenDPD framework, T-Trans DPD achieves superior simulated ACPR, EVM, and NMSE metrics compared to state-of-the-art models, demonstrating its effectiveness for wideband PA applications.},
